quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  55,55,"So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny?"
  55,56,"In them are women limiting [their] glances,{1} untouched{2} before them by man or jinnī -",1:[To their own mates, i.e., being chaste and modest.],2:[Literally, they have not been caused to bleed by loss of virginity.]
  55,57,"So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny? -"
  56,46,"And they used to persist in the great violation,{1}",1:[i.e., shirk (association with Allāh) or disbelief.]
  56,47,"And they used to say, "
  56,48,"And our forefathers [as well]?"
  59,22,"He is Allāh, other than whom there is no deity, Knower of the unseen and the witnessed.{1} He is the Entirely Merciful, the Especially Merciful.",1:[See footnotes to 6:73.]
  59,23,"He is Allāh, other than whom there is no deity, the Sovereign,{1} the Pure,{2} the Perfection,{3} the Grantor of Security,{4} the Overseer,{5} the Exalted in Might,{6} the Compeller,{7} the Superior.{8} Exalted is Allāh above whatever they associate with Him.",1:[And owner of everything in existence.],2:[i.e., transcendent above any aspect belonging to His creation.  Also, the possessor and grantor of blessings.],3:[Literally, \"Free\" from any imperfection.  Also, \"Peace\" or \"Soundness.\"],4:[And safety, i.e., reassurance that His promise is always fulfilled.  Also, He who bestows faith.],5:[i.e., who observes, guards and protects.  Also, \"the Criterion.\"],6:[Refer to footnote in 2:129.],7:[Whose irresistible force is without limitation; the one above all things who compels the creation to be as He wills it.  Also, \"the Amender\" or \"the Rectifier\" who repairs, restores, completes or sets something right once again, out of His mercy.],8:[Supreme, complete and perfect in His essence, attributes and actions.]
  59,24,"He is Allāh, the Creator,{1} the Producer,{2} the Fashioner;{3} to Him belong the best names.{4} Whatever is in the heavens and earth is exalting Him. And He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise.{5}",1:[i.e., He who destined existence for His creation.],2:[i.e., He who brings His creation into existence.],3:[i.e., He who gives every creation its particular form.],4:[Refer to the final paragraphs of the \"Introduction\" for a brief discussion of these attributes.],5:[Refer to footnote in 6:18.]
  61,10,"O you who have believed, shall I guide you to a transaction that will save you from a painful punishment?"
  61,11,"[It is that] you believe in Allāh and His Messenger and strive in the cause of Allāh with your wealth and your lives. That is best for you, if you only knew."
  61,12,"He will forgive for you your sins and admit you to gardens beneath which rivers flow and pleasant dwellings in gardens of perpetual residence. That is the great attainment."
  62,7,"But they will not wish for it, ever, because of what their hands have put forth. And Allāh is Knowing of the wrongdoers."
  62,8,"Say, "
  62,9,"O you who have believed, when [the adhān] is called for the prayer on the day of Jumuʿah [Friday], then proceed to the remembrance of Allāh and leave trade. That is better for you, if you only knew."
  63,4,"And when you see them, their forms please you, and if they speak, you listen to their speech. [They are] as if they were pieces of wood propped up{1} - they think that every shout is against them. They are the enemy, so beware of them. May Allāh destroy them; how are they deluded?",1:[i.e., bodies with empty minds and empty hearts.]
  63,5,"And when it is said to them, "
  63,6,"It is all the same for them whether you ask forgiveness for them or do not ask forgiveness for them; never will Allāh forgive them. Indeed, Allāh does not guide the defiantly disobedient people."
